<div>
  <p>
    This demo uses the
    <code>&lt;picture&gt;</code>
    element with a
    <code>&lt;source&gt;</code>
    for AVIF and WebP.</p><p>The
    <code>&lt;img&gt;</code>
    element uses a JPEG as a fallback. This demo uses the same image resolution
    for all devices as it does not use any
    <code>srcset</code>
    or
    <code>sizes</code>.
  </p>
  <div class="gallery">
    <div class="large">
      <picture>
        <source type="image/avif" srcset="/images/image-1280-lossy.avif" />
        <source type="image/webp" srcset="/images/image-1280-lossy.webp" />
        <img
          alt="Photograph of a group of pedestrians crossing the street."
          width="1280"
          height="852"
          src="/images/image-1280-lossy.jpg"
        />
      </picture>
    </div>
  </div>
